HEADWORD: Harridan
<hw>Har"ri*dan</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧r"r⟦icr⟧*d⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>haridelle</ets> a worn-out horse, jade.]</ety> <def>A
worn-out strumpet; a vixenish woman; a hag.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such a weak, watery, wicked old <qex>harridan</qex>, substituted
for the pretty creature I had been used to see.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>harried</ent>⟦br⟧
